    <string name="info_changed_file_policy_title">Changed-file policy</string>
    <string name="info_changed_file_policy_body">FolderVault is built for files that rarely change. When a file you\'ve already backed up gets edited, this setting decides whether to upload it as a new timestamped copy, overwrite the previous upload, or skip the change.</string>
    <string name="info_retention_policy_title">Retention policy</string>
    <string name="info_retention_policy_body">When files change repeatedly, copies accumulate in the cloud. Retention lets FolderVault prune older copies — keep only the last N versions, or only versions newer than N days. "Keep all" never deletes anything automatically.</string>
    <string name="info_encryption_title">Encryption</string>
    <string name="info_encryption_body">When enabled, your files are encrypted on this device before being uploaded. Google Drive only sees scrambled data; only FolderVault on a device with your password can read them back. If you forget the password, the backup cannot be recovered.</string>

